Noto Serif
==========

Self-hosted to avoid hot-linking Google Fonts (which would send every
visitor's IP to Google — a GDPR concern — and require a third-party origin
in the Content-Security-Policy).

Files:
  NotoSerif-latin.woff2      Latin subset (U+0000–00FF + common punctuation)
  NotoSerif-latin-ext.woff2  Latin Extended subset

These cover the en/fr/es interface. They are the regular (400) upright
weight, version v33, extracted from the Google Fonts CDN's woff2 build of
Noto Serif. To refresh, fetch the per-subset woff2 referenced by
https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Noto+Serif (with a modern browser
User-Agent) and keep the @font-face unicode-ranges in styles/theme.scss in
sync.

